      "result": {
        "justification": "The patient uses a walker and rolling equipment at home per social work note (10/31/2019), indicating fall risk. No anticoagulants are documented during hospitalization, but the patient is on multiple medications including furosemide and carvedilol which can contribute to hypotension and fall risk (medication lists from 2025). The inpatient notes from 10/30 to 11/04/2019 document oxygen use at 2 L/min on 10/30 and 10/31 but none on 11/01 and 11/04, indicating transient respiratory vulnerability. The patient was alert and oriented with family support, reducing cognitive safety concerns. No documented history of major bleeding or anticoagulant use was found. These risks are relevant for ongoing management to prevent falls, monitor respiratory status, and avoid bleeding complications.",
        "medical_risks": "fall propensity, medication-related bleeding risk, respiratory vulnerability"
      }
