        "other_pertinent_information": "The patient is a 72-year-old female with a history of right renal mass diagnosed in 2019, confirmed as renal cell carcinoma, for which she underwent a right hand-assisted laparoscopic radical nephrectomy on 10/30/2019 without complications. She has a history of essential hypertension, type 2 diabetes mellitus, hyperlipidemia, gastroesophageal reflux disease without esophagitis, and familial hypercholesterolemia. She is status post hysterectomy and cesarean section with one vaginal delivery. Socially, she is married, lives with her spouse, has adult children, uses a cane for ambulation, and has arranged for home health services post-hospital discharge. No recent echocardiogram, mammogram, Pap smear, or colonoscopy were documented."
